  <h2>FAQ: Duplicate Line Removal</h2>
  <p><strong>Can I undo the deduplication?</strong> Yes — keep your original list. Our tool only outputs deduplicated results; it doesn't modify your source.</p>

  <p><strong>What if I want to see which lines were duplicated?</strong> Our tool shows the clean unique result. If you need detailed duplicate reports, you may need a spreadsheet application like Excel with pivot table analysis.</p>

  <p><strong>Does it handle whitespace-only differences?</strong> If you have "Apple" and "Apple " (with trailing space), they're treated as different by default. Use our <a href="/tools/remove-extra-spaces/">Remove Extra Spaces tool</a> first to normalize whitespace.</p>

  <p><strong>Can I deduplicate a large dataset?</strong> Yes. There's no practical file size limit. Even datasets with millions of lines are deduplicated instantly in your browser.</p>

